      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "6673767f6c80ef4e",
      "text": "Is a toppled plantation autopoietic and allopoietic at the same time? A combination of human intent and natural patterns of growth, disruption, interruption, eruption? What order do Forming, Creating, Healing take place? Simultaneously?  Does this represent three different states or elements of a single state?  How is forming different than creating?  Is healing the desired state? Do they tumble from [[Forming]], [[Creating]], [[Healing]] into Healing, Forming, Creating and onward into Creating, Forming, Healing?  Each taking a turn at initiating the process?  "
