        "text": "What does it mean to be self-creating?  Is it possible to be self-creating, or is any organism composed of so many other organisms that a sense of self is always a sense of collective creation?  Does that collective have agency- capacity for awareness, advocacy and action or does this remain a miracle of life-creation?\n\nIs a toppled plantation autopoietic and allopoietic at the same time? A combination of human intent and natural patterns of growth, disrupted, interrupted, erupted?  Forming, Creating, Healing- what order does this take place? Simultaneously?  In what way does this represent three different states or elements of a single state?  How is forming different than creating?  Is healing the desired state? Do they tumble from Forming, Creating, Healing into Healing, Forming, Creating and onward into Creating, Forming, Healing?  Each taking a turn at initiating the process?  Is consciousness of creation essential or irrelevant?  "
